Usage
======

The installation has following options. 

./setup.sh  <options>
-j  "username /path/to/install/jdk"
-m  "username /path/to/isntall/mongodb"
-g  "username /path/to/copy/gns.jar"

The arguments to the options must be specified with double quotes. 


Pre-requisites
==============

1. host.txt file with list of hostnames (sample file in the repository)
2. pssh / pscp tools. You can download it from here
http://www.theether.org/pssh/


Note
-----
1. pscp/ssh can fail if the keys are not added in the ssh path. To add the desired keys in your path.
$ ssh-add <key.filename> 

